# Agent Monitors specifications

This repository has a **canonical, code-verified specification set in `docs/specs/`**
(index: `docs/specs/README.md`). It is the source of truth for *intended* behavior and marks each
rule as *current* vs *target*.

**Read only the one doc that matches the task at hand — do not read the whole set.** Relevance map:

- `docs/specs/001-monitor-definition.md` — `MONITOR.md` files, frontmatter schema, monitor identity
- `docs/specs/002-runtime-delivery.md` — runtime tick & scheduling, notify dispatch, event
  persistence, session projection, hook delivery, daemon/IPC, host adapters
- `docs/specs/003-source-plugins.md` — the source-plugin contract and the bundled sources
- `docs/specs/004-validation-testing.md` — validation surfaces and required test scenarios
- `docs/specs/005-cli-reference.md` — the `agentmonitors` command surface
- `docs/specs/000-principles.md` — the invariants (PP/SP/AP/BP/NP) the rest cite
- `docs/specs/roadmap.md` — known current→target gaps; `docs/specs/glossary.md` — terminology

When code and a spec disagree, the spec states which behavior is current vs target. When you change
behavior, update the matching numbered doc and add a `docs/specs/spec-changelog.md` entry (process in
`docs/specs/004-validation-testing.md` §5–6).
